rd]],<br>[[California]],<br>United States\n| Brandon David McInerney, 14\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 15-year-old [[Lawrence Fobes King]] was shot in the head twice by 14-year-old classmate Brandon McInerney in the [[E.O. Green Junior High School]] computer lab in [[Oxnard, California]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://miamiherald.typepad.com/gaysouthflorida/2008/02/gaysoflacom-rem.html|title=\"GaySoFloridacom remembers Lawrence \"Larry\" King \u2013 A Young Hero\"|work=[[Miami Herald]]|date=2008-02-19|accessdate=2008-02-23}}</ref> King was transported to [[St. John's Regional Medical Center (California)|St. John's Regional Medical Center]] in Oxnard under serious condition. Examiners declared King [[Brain death|brain dead]] the following day.<ref name=\"latimes2/14/08\">Saillant, Catherine, Griggs, Gregory (February 14, 2008). \"Student is declared brain dead; Lawrence King, 15, was shot and wounded at an Oxnard campus Tuesday. A classmate faces murder charge.\" ''[[Los Angeles Times]]''. pg. B1.</ref> It was suspected that the motivation of the shooting was McInerney suspecting King was [[gay]], in which a [[hate crime]] charge was filed.<ref name=\"Newsweek\">{{cite web|last=Setoodeh |first=Ramin |title=Young, Gay and Murdered |url=http://www.newsweek.com/id/147790&GT1=43002 |work=[[Newsweek]] |date=2008-07-19 |accessdate=2008-07-23 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080722131056/http://www.newsweek.com/id/147790%26GT1%3D43002 |archivedate=July 22, 2008 |url-status=dead }}</ref> McInerney was sentenced to 21 years of prison on the charge of second-degree murder. \n|-\n| February 25, 2008\n| [[Leizhou]],<br>[[Guangdong]],<br>[[China]]\n| Chen Wenzhen\n| 3 dead\n| 4 injured\n| Chen Wenzhen, a [[Dropping out|school drop-out]] with mental illness, attacked six students with a knife at Leizhou No. 2 Middle School, in [[Leizhou]], [[China]], killing two of them. He then committed suicide by stabbing himself in the abdomen and jumping out of a window in the fifth floor.<ref name=\"xinhaunet226\">{{cite web |title = 3 dead, 4 injured in school killing in S. China |author= Liang, Yan |publisher= [[Xinhuanet]]|date = February 26, 2008| url =http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-02/26/content_7669100.htm|accessdate = 2009-05-07}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 6, 2008\n| [[Mobile, Alabama]], United States\n| Jajuan Holmes, 18\n| 1 dead\n|\n| Jajuan Holmes, an 18-year-old student on suspension, walked into the gym area at [[Davidson High School (Mobile, Alabama)|Davidson High School]] and shot himself in front of 150 students. The school was put on lockdown for the day.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/0,2933,335673,00.html |title=Student kills self in front of 150 classmates at Alabama High School |publisher=Foxnews.com |date=2008-03-06 |accessdate=2011-03-12 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090222050715/http://www.foxnews.com/story/0%2C2933%2C335673%2C00.html |archivedate=February 22, 2009 }}</ref>\n|-\n| April 16, 2008\n| [[Fresno, California]], United States\n| Jesus Carrizales, 17\n| 1 dead\n| 1 injured\n| Carrizales struck a Roosevelt High School resource police officer on the head with a baseball bat, and then the officer fatally shot him once in the chest.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxnews.com/story/2008/04/17/relatives-say-school-failed-to-help-depressed-fresno-student-killed-by-police.html|title=Relatives Say School Failed to Help Depressed Fresno Student Killed By Police|date=17 April 2008|website=foxnews.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| April 28, 2008\n| [[Meyzieu]], France\n| Philippe, 15\n|\n| 4 injured\n| A 15-year-old student, whose name was only revealed as Philippe, stabbed a girl and two boys at Olivier de Serres middle school in [[Meyzieu]], just after he had sent an SMS to a friend stating: \"I will kill them.\" The boy, who was himself wounded during the attack, then escaped, but was arrested by police one hour later. Philippe, who was said to have been inspired by American school shootings and had planne