AT]] member, after raising the weapon at an officer. The weapon was a pellet gun.<ref name=ctvlist>{{cite news|title=List of major incidents at North American schools|work=[[Canadian Press]]|publisher=[[CTV television network|CTV.ca]]|date=2006-09-13|url=http://www.ctv.ca/servlet/ArticleNews/story/CTVNews/20060913/violence_timeline_060913/20060913/|accessdate=2006-09-14}}</ref>\n|-\n| February 23, 2006\n| [[Roseburg, Oregon]], United States\n| Vincent Wayne Leodoro, 14\n|\n| 1 injured\n| 14-year-old Vincent Leodoro shot 16-year-old fellow student Joseph Monti in the back four times with a [[10mm]] [[semi-automatic pistol]], critically injuring him, in the courtyard of [[Roseburg High School]] in [[Roseburg, Oregon]]. He was found guilty of attempted murder and assault in July 2006, and will be held in prison until he turns 25 years old.<ref>{{cite web|title=Teen found guilty in Roseburg High shooting|url=http://www.katu.com/news/3633746.html|publisher=KATU|date=June 29, 2006|accessdate=February 1, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Teenager faces charges in Oregon high school shooting\n|url=http://seattletimes.com/html/localnews/2002826654_weboreshooting24.html|newspaper=Seattle Times|date=February 24, 2006|accessdate=February 1, 2013}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 14, 2006\n| [[Reno]], [[Nevada]], United States\n| James Scott Newman, 14\n|\n| 2 injured\n| [[Pine Middle School shooting]]. 14-year-old student James Newman brought a [[.38 ACP|.38-caliber]] [[revolver]] to Pine Middle School in [[Reno]], [[Nevada]], and shot and injured two students at random in the school's hallway before being restrained by a physical education teacher.<ref name=\"KOLOTV\">{{cite news\n|first = Koula\n|last = Gianulias\n|author2=Kara Tsuboi |author3=Ed Pearce\n |title = Reno School Shooting Team Report\n|url = http://www.kolotv.com/home/headlines/2461261.html\n|work=\n|publisher= [[KOLO-TV]]\n|location = [[Reno, Nevada]], United States\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n }}</ref><ref name=\"LasVegasReview\">{{cite news\n|first = Sandra\n|last = Chereb\n|author2=Kara Tsuboi |author3=Ed Pearce\n |title = School shooting arraignment delayed in school\n|url = http://www.reviewjournal.com/lvrj_home/2006/Mar-18-Sat-2006/news/6431035.html\n|agency = [[The Associated Press]]\n|work= [[Las Vegas Review-Journal]]\n|publisher= Sherman Frederick\n|location = [[Las Vegas, Nevada]], United States\n|date = 2006-03-18\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n|quote =\n }}</ref> Newman was charged as a juvenile for two counts of [[Battery (crime)|battery]] with a deadly weapon and was sentenced to [[house arrest]] and 200 hours of [[community service]].<ref name=\"WashingtonPost\">{{cite news\n|first = Scott\n|last = Sonner\n|title = Teen Gets House Arrest in Nev. Shooting\n|url = https://www.washingtonpost.com/wp-dyn/content/article/2006/05/26/AR2006052602039_Technorati.html\n|work= [[The Washington Post]]\n|publisher= [[Katharine Weymouth]]\n|location = Washington, D.C., United States\n|date = 2006-05-26\n|accessdate = 2008-11-21\n|quote =\n }}</ref>\n|-\n| June 6, 2006\n| [[Los Angeles, California]], United States\n|\n| 1 dead\n|\n| 17-year-old Venice High School junior Augustine Contreras was shot and killed in one of the school's parking lots shortly after the day's classes ended. He was shot after he went to the aid of his brothers, who were involved in a fight with several other young men. The fight was reportedly stemmed from a local gang dispute between Latino and black students. Two arrests were made but the suspects were released shortly thereafter.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://pqasb.pqarchiver.com/latimes/access/1049088491.html?dids=1049088491:1049088491&FMT=ABS&FMTS=ABS:FT&type=current&date=Jun+06%2C+2006&author=Amanda+Covarrubias+and+Lynn+Doan&pub=Los+Angeles+Times&desc=Student+Fatally+Shot+at+Venice+High%3B+The+17-year-old+was+killed+after+a+campus+fistfight+involving+Latinos+and+blacks.+Some+fear+a+resumption+of+gang+violence.&pqatl=google |title=Student Fatally Shot at Venice 